lict resolution used to control water usage; building of troughs and wells; installing of pumps far from residences; building irrigation canals for the dry season; replacing excavated material; providing compensation to displaced persons; using drainage works; replanting trees; integrated management of water resources; avoiding prolonged food storage; ensuring that imported animals are disease-free (have a certificate of health); encouraging traditional/local pastoral practices/indigenous knowledge and technical innovation, and improving traditional infrastructure; restoring the vegetal cover; establishing a waste management plan; promoting the use of organic fertilizer (manure); making selective site choices; wearing protective gear to avoid pesticide poisoning; avoiding the introduction of exotic species even if the risk is low; treating wastewater according to international norms; and raising sensitivity of sexually transmitted diseases among workers.
